<h1>Expressing Time</h1>

<p>
To express a time the counter suffixes <a href="grammar-counter-ji.html">@KJ{{time}}<a> (o'clock)
and <a href="grammar-counter-bun.html">@KJ{{part}}<a> (minutes) are used.
</p>

<p>
To ask about the time or a time interval, @HI{{nann}} is used with the above counter suffixes.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{now^what^time}}desuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{7@KJ{{time}}10@KJ{{part}}desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      What time is it now?
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      It's 7:10.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

